               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18470816-name-1004" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18470816-name-1004" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18470816-name-1004" type="surname" value="LUCAS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18470816-name-1004" type="given" value="JOSEPH"></interp>JOSEPH LUCAS.</persName>
                  </hi> I live in Suffolk-street, Bethnal-green. I was at Hackney church when the prisoner was married to my sister Rebecca—he lived with her after the marriage—I saw her about nine days ago.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. PAYNE</hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> Was she married in her right name? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> I do not know—I cannot answer whether Rebecca Lucas was her right name—I know her mother was not my mother, as I am told—I do not know that she was treated as an illegitimate child—she went by the name of Rebecca Lucas—I never heard her called anything else.</p>
